Package repository

Interface Repository<T,ID>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of entity that the repository will manage (e.g., Patient, Medicine).
ID - The type of the unique identifier for the entity (e.g., String, Integer).
All Known Implementing Classes:
AppointmentRepository, DoctorAvailabilityRepository, MedicalRecordRepository, MedicineRepository, PatientRepository, StaffRepository
public interface Repository<T,ID>
The Repository interface defines the basic operations that can be performed on an entity in a repository. It is a generic interface that works with any entity type T and a unique identifier type ID. Implementations of this interface should provide the actual behavior for managing the entities.

      Parameters:

      Returns:

      Finds an entity by its unique identifier.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      An Optional containing the entity if found, or an empty Optional if not found.

      Parameters:
